
[1]argumentation

   ARGUMENTA'TION, n. Reasoning; the act of reasoning; the act of
   inventing or forming reasons, making inductions, drawing conclusions,
   and applying them to the case in discussion. The operation of inferring
   propositions, not known or admitted as true, from facts or principles
   known, admitted, or proved to be true.
